The paper proposes a novel loss function for value function learning in reinforcement learning, which can be optimized using gradient-based methods. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which further supports the likelihood of it belonging to cs.LG and cs.AI. The paper deals with optimization and convergence guarantees, which suggests that it may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of sampled transitions, which suggests that it may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
